definition.value: A member of the class of quinazolines that is quinazoline which is substituted by a benzylnitrilo group at position 4.

A member of the class of 1,2,4-triazines in which the triazine ring is substituted at positions 3, 5, and 6 by pyridin-2-yl, ([biphenyl]-4-ylmethyl)amin, and methyl groups, respectively. It is an activator of the hypoxia inducible factor (HIF) pathway.
a scyllo-inositol phosphate compound having a phosphate group in the 5-position and amino groups in place of hydroxy groups in the 1- and 3-positions.
